# Kwery Cross-Platform Comparison

## Tool Matrix

| Platform | Candles/Prices | Trades | Order Book | Markets List |
|----------|----------------|--------|------------|--------------|
| Polymarket | `polymarket_candles` | `polymarket_trades` | `polymarket_orderbook` | `polymarket_markets` |
| Kalshi | `kalshi_prices` | - | `kalshi_orderbook` | `kalshi_markets` |
| Binance Spot | `binance_candles` | - | - | `binance_spot_markets` |
| Binance Futures | `binance_candles` (source=binance_futures) | - | - | `binance_futures_markets` |
| Hyperliquid | `hyperliquid_candles` | `hyperliquid_trades` | - | `hyperliquid_markets` |
| Chainlink | `chainlink_candles` | - | - | - |

## Key Workflows

### Oracle lag (Chainlink vs Binance)
```
chainlink_candles(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", limit=168)
binance_candles(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", limit=168)
```
Lag in Chainlink feeds means prediction markets may misprice at settlement.

### Basis and funding arbitrage
```
binance_candles(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", source="binance")
binance_candles(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", source="binance_futures")
binance_funding(symbol="BTC", limit=500)
```

### Prediction market vs derivatives sentiment
```
polymarket_candles(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", token_id="<clob_token_up>")
binance_funding(symbol="BTC", limit=500)
binance_oi(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", limit=500)
```
Convergence = high conviction. Divergence = potential mean-reversion trade.

### Hyperliquid vs Binance premium
```
hyperliquid_candles(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", limit=168)
binance_candles(symbol="BTC", interval="1h", source="binance_futures", limit=168)
```

## Notes

- Always use the same `symbol`, `interval`, and time window across platforms
- Use `binance_spot_markets` / `binance_futures_markets` to discover available tickers
- Free 7d - Pro 14d - Business 31d across all tools
